ChangeLog for Lime Parser Generator
====================================

2026-05-15  Greg Burd  <greg@burd.me>

	* limpar.c, lime.c: Honor user-defined YYLLOC_DEFAULT macro on
	every reduce, per Bison's documented signature
	(Current, Rhs, N).  When the macro is defined in the grammar's
	%include block (or any header included therein), yy_reduce
	builds a YYLOCATIONTYPE Rhs[YYNRHS_MAX+1] from the just-popped
	stack slots and calls the user macro to compute the LHS
	location.  When undefined, the prior built-in default (Rhs[1]
	via slot reuse for non-empty rules; lookahead loc for empty
	rules) is preserved byte-for-byte -- zero behavior change for
	grammars that don't override.  YYRHSLOC(Rhs, K) provided as
	((Rhs)[K]) so user macros using Bison's documented YYRHSLOC
	indirection also work.  YYNRHS_MAX is emitted by lime as the
	longest RHS in the grammar; fixed on-stack buffer, no VLA.

	* limpar.c (ParseInit): Zero-initialise yystack[0].yyloc.  The
	sentinel slot is the Rhs[0] source for the very first reduce
	when a user-defined YYLLOC_DEFAULT runs (e.g. an empty rule
	fired before any token shifts).  Pre-existing default-only
	code never read it; same convention as the existing
	yyLookaheadLoc zero-init.

	* tests/test_yylloc_default*: New focused test grammar +
	driver.  %location_type {struct span} carrying {start, end}
	byte offsets; YYLLOC_DEFAULT computes Bison's stock span
	(Rhs[1].start..Rhs[N].end with Rhs[0].end empty-rule
	fallback).  Discriminator sub-test reduces list ::= list C
	across multiple tokens; LHS span .end must march forward to
	each successive token.  Fails on the prior slot-reuse default;
	passes on the new override path.

	* docs/MIGRATION_FROM_BISON.md: New "Location override" section
	documenting the YYLLOC_DEFAULT signature, YYRHSLOC, the
	empty-rule fallback, and the post-action timing difference vs
	Bison.  Directive-mapping rows for %locations and
	YYLLOC_DEFAULT.  New Common Gotcha #9 on Lime's post-action
	orderng: @$ inside an action body reads the pre-override
	slot-reuse value; post-override is observed via @N in the
	next reduce.

	* man/lime_grammar.5: Expand "Location Tracking" subsection
	with %location_type, the @<rhsalias> / @<lhsalias> / @$ macro
	aliases, and the YYLLOC_DEFAULT override contract.  Backfills
	coverage of P0-NEW-2 (location threading, shipped 2026-05-13)
	as well as the new P0-NEW-6 override.

	* Lime-Requests.txt: P1-6 ("YYLLOC_DEFAULT override") marked
	SHIPPED.

	* Note: this entry only covers the P0-NEW-6 commit; the
	ChangeLog is otherwise 37 commits behind HEAD.  Backfilling
	earlier P0-NEW-2/3/4/5 + P1-NEW-1 entries is a separate
	hygiene task.

2026-04-30  Greg Burd  <greg@burd.me>

	* Project restructuring: move shell scripts into scripts/, move
	Doxyfile into docs/, add docs/Makefile and docs/README.md, add
	ChangeLog, add CI configurations, clean up agent artifacts.

	* Remove agent-generated report files (VALIDATION_RESULTS.md,
	VALIDATION.md, README_VALIDATION.md, PERFORMANCE_REPORT.md,
	LINT_FORMAT_GUIDE.md, CLAUDE.md) and stray test artifacts.

	* Add .agent/README.md for tool-agnostic AI assistant context.

2026-04-29  Greg Burd  <greg@burd.me>

	* tests/test_strategy_priority_extended.c,
	tests/test_grammar_context.c, tests/test_extension_registry.c:
	New test files covering priority disambiguation, grammar context
	stack management, and extension registry operations.  499 new
	assertions bringing extension framework coverage above 90%.

	* contrib/oracle_compat/, contrib/sqlite_compat/,
	contrib/duckdb_features/, contrib/mysql_compat/,
	contrib/edn_literals/, contrib/xml_query/: SQL dialect extension
	examples demonstrating the runtime grammar extension API.

	* examples/llm_oracle/: LLM-based disambiguation oracle example.

	* docs/EXTENSION_PERFORMANCE.md, docs/ALGORITHM.md,
	docs/COMPARISON.md, docs/MIGRATION_FROM_BISON.md,
	docs/MIGRATION_FROM_YACC.md: Reference documentation for the
	extension framework, LALR(1) algorithm, and migration guides.

	* man/lime.1, man/lime_grammar.5: Man pages for the lime command
	and grammar file format.

	* bench/extension_overhead.c, bench/BENCHMARK_RESULTS.md:
	Extension overhead microbenchmarks (25 benchmarks, fast-path
	119 ns, worst-case 1.4 us).

	* include/conflict.h: Moved from src/ to include/ (public API).

	* Doxyfile: Added with 120+ function annotations across 8 headers.

2026-04-28  Greg Burd  <greg@burd.me>

	* limpar.c: Fix unused-variable warning in yy_destructor when no
	%destructor directives defined.  Fix "comparison is always true"
	warning in ParseFinalize by setting YY_MIN_DSTRCTR to nsymbol.

	* examples/calc/: Calculator example with runtime extension
	loading via dlopen.  Base 4-operation calculator plus a shared
	library (libcalc_power.so) for the ^ operator.

2026-04-27  Greg Burd  <greg@burd.me>

	* tests/test_coverage_boost.c: Rewrite JIT policy and conflict
	tests to use current API (JITMetrics/JITPolicyConfig).

	* src/parse_context.c: Implement parse_begin, parse_end,
	parse_get_snapshot, parse_token, snap_find_shift_action,
	snap_find_reduce_action.

	* src/jit_tokenizer.c: Fix missing #include <stdio.h>.

	* src/glr.c, src/utf8.c, src/lime_ast.c, src/jit_tokenizer.c:
	New modules for GLR parsing, UTF-8 handling, AST directives,
	and JIT-compiled tokenization.

	* lime.c, limpar.c: Add location tracking, error recovery, and
	AST directive support.

	* bench/bench_grammar.lime, bench/bench_grammar.y: Benchmark
	grammars for Lime vs Bison performance comparison.

2026-04-24  Greg Burd  <greg@burd.me>

	* lime.c: Add -L (lint) and -F (format) flags for grammar
	validation and consistent formatting.  Lint checks module
	metadata, symbol exports, unused symbols.  Format generates
	consistently styled output.

	* lime.c: Add %module_name, %module_version, %module_description,
	%require, %export, %import directives for Bison-style module
	metadata.

	* tools/lime-compose: Complete rewrite for directive-based module
	format with topological dependency resolution.

	* tools/convert_format.py: Migration tool from Markdown+YAML
	format to directive format.

	* docs/MODULE_FORMAT.md: Module format specification.

	* src/merkle_tree.{h,c}, src/dependency_resolver.{h,c},
	src/parser_composition.{h,c}: Merkle-tree-based modular parser
	composition system with SHA-256 content addressing, SemVer
	dependency tracking, and topological sort.

	* examples/datalog/, examples/xpath/, examples/xquery/,
	examples/mongodb/: New language parser examples in literate
	format.

	* examples/pg_modular/: PostgreSQL grammar split into 35 literate
	modules with dependency graph.

	* tests/test_merkle_tree.c, tests/test_dependency_resolver.c,
	tests/test_parser_composition.c, tests/test_random_composition.c:
	106 tests for composition infrastructure.

2026-04-23  Greg Burd  <greg@burd.me>

	* examples/pg/gram.lime: Complete PostgreSQL grammar conversion
	from Bison format.  782 non-terminals, 3584 production rules,
	2406 semantic actions, 0 conflicts.

	* examples/pg/tokens.lime, examples/pg/types.lime: Token
	definitions and type declarations extracted from gram.y.

	* examples/pg/tokenize.c, examples/pg/tokenize.h: PostgreSQL-
	compatible tokenizer with all 6 string types and keyword lookup.

	* examples/pg/pg_gram_helpers.c, examples/pg/pg_gram_helpers.h:
	41 helper functions ported from gram.y.

	* test_harness/: Python test framework for parser comparison
	(Lime vs Bison) with AST comparison support.
